social_posts.post_text: These little girls are so proud to be big sisters — cutest thing ever. 🫶🏼

Last week of family sessions and full week of work until 2023!! I’m so grateful for each and every family I’ve gotten the privilege to photograph this year and especially this holiday season. My heart is full! 🫶🏼
Closing out the year with a total banger 🤩 such a gorgeous day for Cody and Tori — more to come!
Gorgeous rainy day maternity session in Pasadena for Trish and Luke. 🖤

They met their freshman year of college at LMU, so we took it back to where it all began — including the exact classroom and seats they sat in when they first met. This session will go down as one of my favorite engagement sessions of all time. Tug on my rom-com heart strings why don’t ya! 🖤

12 years ago today Ashley Burns Photography was born. Thank you to every single person who has been along for this ride, especially those who have been there since the beginning and never wavered — I wouldn’t be here without you. I truly couldn’t imagine doing anything else. 🫶🏼
Unbelievably stunning session for Abbi and Aneesh. You can feel their happiness in every photo and couldn’t stop smiling while editing their session. ✨
Soaking in every bit of this season with Brian and Honey as we go into the week of Christmas and Hanukkah. The best time of the year 🫶🏼
My whole heart. 🖤

1 year married, 9 years together. Happy Anniversary to my favorite person in the world. I love the life we are building. All these years later and I still obsess over you. Even when you walk on the rug with your shoes on. 🖤

Gratefully saying goodbye to 2022 (good riddance, you were hard!) and welcoming 2023 with open arms — feeling hopeful (🤞🏼) for a lot of good change, and trusting the divine timing of things so I can take a step back to breathe and enjoy the ride a little more. Sending you and yours a happy and safe new year. Hope to see many of you in 2023! 🫶🏼

Finally getting around to sharing this absolute stunner of a wedding for two of my dearest friends! It was the perfect weekend filled with love, family and friends in Emma and Julien’s favorite place, Los Alamos. It was such an honor to photograph your day. 🫶🏼
Spring mini session sign ups are coming this week. Also, I love The Maupin’s 🫶🏼
Tani and Shane’s NYE wedding was the perfect way to end 2022 and begin 2023. These high school sweethearts are married! There are no words how happy I am for these two. 🤍
Wedding season begins next week with these two in Tulum 🌴 beyond excited and grateful for all the work travel to come this year!
New favorite unlocked 🔓: snowy engagement sessions ❄️ give me all of the cozy, winter sessions! Obsessed.
Welcome party perfection in Tulum🌴 it’s wedding day for Michelle and Jason!!

The most epic weekend documenting the most beautiful love story! I cannot wait to share Jason and Michelle’s wedding day with you all. 🤍 
#tulum #tulumwedding #destinationphotographer #tulumweddingphotographer #mexicowedding #destinationwedding #weddingphotographer
In-home newborn sessions are some of my favorite weekday sessions I do! Especially when there’s beautiful natural light like The Esselen’s home. Jackson is here and he is the most perfect angel. 🤍
Some black and white frames of The Sheppards in Portland — I miss being a quick ten minute drive from these dear friends. 🤍

Sharing the long awaited wedding of Jason and Michelle in Tulum, Mexico! I feel like there has to be multiple posts to really unpack the absolute magic of this day. A shaman at their ceremony, a venue in the jungle, a fire show for guests during the reception, speeches that left not a dry eye in the house. Being a part of this wedding weekend was such a highlight in my career. These two are one of the most gracious, loving, giving and FUN couples I’ve ever had the pleasure of working with! You can really tell how amazing people are based on who they surround themselves around and I can honestly say the people in their lives are just as great as they are. 10000/10 wedding. Ready to go back. 🫶🏼
Realistic day in my life! 🫶🏼 My day started at 6:45am today and ended at 7:30pm. Let me know if you guys want more of this kind of content!
The unpredictable weather this weekend still made for such gorgeous sessions — love how they all came out 😍 we rallied and it paid off! Beyond obsessed.

The one perfect-weather-day we’ve gotten in a while (I know, shocker for SoCal) and it happened to fall on Ava and Dillon’s engagement session while they were in town from Dallas. DID NOT DISAPPOINT 🤍
Sarah and Drew are the kind of people that validate soulmates exist. I cannot stop smiling thinking about what a fairytale yesterday was — somebody pinch me! Absolute heart explosion. 🤍
Can’t stop thinking about this @moniquelhuillier dress — Sarah was the most beautiful and regal bride. 🥹
These photos are absolute sunshine and deserve to be shared. Kacie and her son Cruz — the perfect duo ☀️
When it starts raining mid-shoot and you roll with it — i swear it’s good karma/luck 🤍 Eric and Nellie crushed it — sharing the B + W’s cause duhhh!

An unreal night chasing light with The Hemmingsen’s. Avery is almost here. 🤍
Rare sighting of me and my husband out in the wild (we’re usually working or in bed by 8pm). #dinklife
Getting that tablescape shot set is very serious business — thanks for the photo @tessbrankerphoto 🤍

Ten slides is not enough to share my favorites from this drop dead gorgeous day — can I have like 50 slides instead? These high school sweethearts would be so happy to know where their story led them. My heart is absolutely bursting at the seams! Some days deserve a “let’s do it again” button. 🤍
Heartfelt speeches will get me every time. 🤍
Can we just have a moment for one of my stunning brides, Julia 😍 such an absolute beaut inside and out!
The Lamson’s are the cutest — just love these. 🤍
Manifesting more elopement perfection in my future ✨
Hi! I feel like it’s been forever. I have so much to catch you all up on and can’t wait to finally share soon. 🫶🏼 (no, I’m not pregnant lol)
Cannot handle little Ezra and his little curls and smile! He loved the camera 😍

social_posts.post_text: 10/10 recommend making out in the elevator on your wedding day. Nellie and Eric were a freakin’ dream ✨ more to come from this day soon!
Finley is here and she is beyond — congrats to The Peterson’s 😍
Going into a double header work weekend and practically living in my car over the next three days. I loooove wedding season 🫶🏼
Not just a professional photographer, but also a professional hair adjuster/fixer/perfect-er 🤪 the brides that know, KNOW I’m hair crazy
Can’t get enough of Maddi and Chad’s maternity session. 🤍
Highly in favor of my couples bringing their pups to their session 🐶 Storm was such a model! His pawwwrents are getting married so soon and I can’t wait!
Just want to shout from every rooftop how much I loved working with this couple 🥲 the day, the couple, their families, the details, the tears — sign me the heck up!

It still blows my mind every time I get to document a milestone in a friends life journey. As much as I know the photos mean a lot to them, it means just as much knowing they’ll get to have these memories documented forever. Obsessing over Cassie’s maternity shoot 🥹 Baby B is almost here!
Stunning details from an absolutely stunning day for Talia and Max ✨
Kayley surrounded by her beautiful boys…and another on the way 🤍🥲

✨LIFE UPDATE✨
Well… lets cut to the chase… Brian is going to be a DOCTOR! For the past few years, Brian has been working towards getting into medical school and I’m so happy to share that he was accepted into an incredible MD program his first cycle of applying (not shocked - hes brilliant!). With this amazing news, comes moving! We bought a beautiful brand new home close to Brian’s medical school. Luckily, we are still in California and I will be able to maintain working with all of my clients and we are only an hour and half away from family and friends. I’m so excited to share this next chapter with you all, and thank you for the support you have shown us and our family! We couldn’t feel more grateful. 🤍

the look of two very happy people who just left their closing signing and get the keys to their first home tomorrow. papers signed, money sent! swipe to see a photo of two year old me at my parents closing signing on their first home. 🤍 #homeowners
These two dreamboats start their wedding weekend tomorrow and I’m so excited for all that is to come. Cannot wait to share their special and beautiful weekend! 🤍
Having my cake and eating it too this weekend 🍰
When your pups are the flower girl and ring bearer 🥲🤍 my heart cannot handle
Me and my work wife @alwaysallegra_ feat. a finger. She is the greatest in the game, no one else compares 🤝🏼 love you forever
Core memory: sleeping on the floor of our new home the first night before all the furniture arrives. PS: don’t mind the rotisserie chicken.
An all-white summer wedding in the sand for Jackie and Scott — magical day for magical people. 🤍
Lover (Ashley’s Version) 🦋💓🪻
I love every time I get to do pregnancy announcements 🥹 obsessed with Jayme and Chris’ announcement photos with their pug babies!

Some of my favorite black and white moments from Cam and Meghan’s stunning day in Santa Barbara 🤍 one of the most trusting, fun, and loving couples I’ve ever gotten the privilege of working with. I’ve said it before, but 10 slides will never be enough — so many favorites!
Too many photos from this night with Tasha and Ben that give me all the heart eyes — the most fun with them 😍
One of my favorite engagement sessions this year. I mean, can they get any more gorgeous?! So excited for Shauna and Ori’s wedding day this fall 🤍
Nick and Mackenzie bringing all of the heat to the beach 🔥 seriously cannot wait for their wedding next summer! Such a beautiful couple.
Loved spending the afternoon with Brianna and James 🤍 they wanted to have their engagement session at home to commemorate their first place together! So excited for their fall wedding 🥰

Took our sterile builder-grade guest bathroom and turned it into a warm and inviting space just by adding and replacing a few things — so happy with the end result 🤩

Limewash paint: Dry Ground by @portolapaints
Chauntel and Collin’s joy-filled proposal can’t help but make you smile and feel the absolute happiness these two felt in that moment. So meant to be and such an incredible surprise. 🤍
Random wedding season iPhone dump from some of your wedding days 🥲 the last one is veryyyy much how I feel after working 10+ hours
Shooting around Greece has been a dream ✨

Some memories of the past two weeks! I brought my mom, aunts and cousin to Europe with me because I shot a wedding in Greece. It turned into the absolute greatest girls trip and such an incredible experience! I couldn’t imagine spending the past couple of weeks with anyone else. They’re the best and my people forever. Grateful for a job that allows me to travel and bring my loved ones along. 🤍
It does not get much more picture perfect than Jenny and Derek, and their day 🤍

Can you believe we only have two months left of 2023?! I’m still completely mind blown over it 🤯 so excited to see everyone’s holiday cards this year from fall minis! They have been somethin special this year 🤍
A beautiful day for a beautiful couple, inside and out — loved being a part of Jeannene and Parker’s wedding day last month 🤍
Absolutely no details were overlooked for Hannah and Raffi’s dream day. 🤍 these two know how to throw a party!!! SO GOOD. Loved working with this amazing couple!
Havin’ their cake, eatin’ it too 🤍 can’t wait to share more of one of my most favorite weddings of all time — Brent and Lauren are absolute dreamboats and here for a good time 🔥
Shooting in Greece at sunrise and sunset for Sara and Nick’s elopement was magical ✨

A spectacularly gorgeous day all around for Shauna and Ori last month in Camarillo ✨🤍 it was my fourth time documenting a wedding in Shauna’s family and it was so beyond special. Loved this day so much!
The look of a pug who is very concerned with her moms work schedule and learning that 2024 is even busier 📸

This time of year is my Super Bowl. I’m stretched super thin, everything is heightened, and the work load is next level. Before entering this season I am always a little nervous with the amount that I take on and then once I’m in it I’m instantly reminded this is why I do what I do. Documenting families year after year is a subtle reminder that I’m constantly in the direction of abundance and where I am supposed to be. You all are so much a part of my story and journey in this life. This time of year is our check in and opportunity to pick up where we left off in your story. I’m so, so grateful for the people that choose me year after year. It’s the gift that keeps on givin’. Love you a whole lot.
These high school sweethearts got married at one of my favorite venues ever @sherwood_country_club 🤍 what a beautiful day this was earlier this month — congrats Jenna and Wade!!!

Layla brought her little camera to her family session and got to take photos alongside me while I photographed her parents! Such a sweet moment shared this fall season and it’s been a joy to watch her grow. I love that she brought her camera along — we might have a budding photographer because her composition was perfect 🥲
At home with The Randolph’s 🤍

Ashley Burns Photography is 13 years old today! I shot my first wedding at 17 years old and haven’t looked back since. It has been the greatest joy of my life being a part of so many wonderful days in so many couples and families stories. Forever grateful for all the people that make up my world, have supported me, cheered me on, and have given me so much assurance that this is exactly what I was put on this earth to do. I always tell my families and couples I love them, and I mean it. I love you. 🫶🏼
Picture perfect black and white winter wedding for Maggie and Corey 🤍 this was a favorite amongst many vendors! Such a blast and so much beauty. Grateful to end the year with such a banger!
Ten years together; two years married today. We’re living the good ol’ days and every year that passes keeps getting better. I can’t wait to grow old with you. 🤍
Merry Christmas from The Kavins — 2023 was the best year 🤍
At sunset with Cori and Mike...and their golden Jane. 🤍 could not be more in love with their session — and seriously can’t wait for their wedding next summer!!
Welcome to the stunning Mehndi + Haldi of Abbi and Aneesh, part of their gorgeous 3-day wedding weekend in Cancun, Mexico. Could photograph this couple til’ the end of time. 🤍

Hard to believe it’s been 5 years since this beautiful couple got married and I documented their special day! They’ve built such a beautiful life together and welcomed their sweet baby boy a little over a year ago. Happy Anniversary, Danica and Brian!! I’m so happy you found each other. 🤍
Shooting this family at Trish’s childhood home was so special and full-circle — I love sessions that hold sentimental meaning so much. How precious are the Esselens?! Love this growing fam! 🥹

Flash photography reception magic with Aneesh and Abbi 🫶🏼 obsessed doesn’t cut it! Steal time away with your photog, post up against a blank wall, and enjoy the moment. The result is always worth it and SO FUN! Are they a vibe or are they a vibe?!
Honey has a little sister. 🤍
That first moment after becoming Mr. and Mrs. 🤍 James and Brianna had such a beautiful day surrounded by SO much love.
